<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="255" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,541,1468]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,458,937,963]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moravec &amp; Trýzna" authorityYear="2022" box="[477,818,937,964]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andreevae" subGenus="Microstenocera">
<emphasis box="[477,631,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[651,674,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[702,818,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">andreevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is immediately distinguished from all species of the genus by its yellow-testaceous metatarsi. For other diagnostic characters see under 
<taxonomicName authority="Moravec &amp; Trýzna, 2022" authorityName="Moravec &amp; Trýzna" authorityYear="2022" box="[1094,1338,973,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borisbubeniki" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Microstenocera">
<emphasis box="[1094,1111,974,999]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1136,1159,974,999]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1184,1338,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">borisbubeniki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,973,999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,973,999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
above, as well as the illustrations here and the original description and illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J." box="[1113,1298,1009,1036]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" refId="ref8780" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec (2007)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="255" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,541,1468]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,494,1045,1071]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[510,594,1045,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–37" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,191,1137]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[151,1436,181,1144]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 36–37. Distribution of the two relevant Pogonostoma (Microstenocera) species in Madagascar. 36—P. (M.) boris- bubeniki sp. nov.; 37— P. (M.) andreevae Moravec." pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moravec &amp; Trýzna" authorityYear="2022" box="[614,948,1045,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andreevae" subGenus="Microstenocera">
<emphasis box="[614,768,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[785,816,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[832,948,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">andreevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the evergreen forest of the Ranomafana National Park in south-eastern part of the Central 
<collectingRegion box="[900,1019,1081,1107]" country="Czech Republic" name="Vysocina" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Highlands</collectingRegion>
. The three known adults were caught along Talatakely touristic circuit in an elevation 
<quantity box="[708,798,1117,1144]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" unit="m" value="1080.0">1080 m</quantity>
, in fact nearby the village of Ranomafana. Despite that Talatakely is characterized as a low montane secondary forest, it maintains amazing biodiversity. 
<taxonomicName authority="Moravec, 2007" authorityName="Moravec" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sawadai" subGenus="Microstenocera">
