<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="255" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,541,1468]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1261,1287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moravec &amp; Trýzna" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,656,1261,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andreevae" subGenus="Microstenocera">
<emphasis box="[322,476,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[493,524,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[540,656,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">andreevae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by the first author (
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J." box="[1159,1326,1261,1287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" refId="ref8780" refString="Moravec, J. (2007) Tiger beetles of Madagascar 1. A monograph of the genus Pogonostoma (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Nakladatelstvi Kabourek, Zlin, 499 pp." type="book" year="2007">Moravec 2007</bibRefCitation>
) from the female 
<typeStatus box="[237,338,1297,1323]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">holotype</typeStatus>
, while the only known male was identified by him from specimens sent for his study by David Kavanaugh (CAS) much later, when the monograph of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1835" box="[793,947,1334,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pogonostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[793,947,1334,1359]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Pogonostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was in press. Consequently, the male was additionally included into the monograph and designated as 
<typeStatus box="[830,924,1369,1395]" pageId="10" pageNumber="255">allotype</typeStatus>
. As only diagnostic characters of the male 
<typeStatus pageId="10" pageNumber="255">allotype</typeStatus>
were illustrated in the monograph, its habitus and metatarsi are illustrated for the first time here (
<figureCitation box="[1303,1432,1405,1431]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1826,1850]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,185,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[165,1421,181,1802]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 25–31. Pogonostoma (Microstenocera) andreevae Moravec, type locality Ranomafana. 25—pronotum, ♀ (CJVB); 26–27—labrum: 26—♀, HT (JWCW, later in ZSM) 27—♀ (CJVB); 28—metatarsus, ♀ (CJVB); 29—male aedeagus, AT (CAS); 30—habitus, ♂, 7.5 mm,AT (CAS); 31—ditto, partial ventral view on testaceous metatarsi. Bars = 1 mm (30–31—im- age credit Rachel Diaz-Bastin, CAS)." pageId="10" pageNumber="255">Figs 30–31</figureCitation>
, photographed in CAS database).
</paragraph>
